The paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for object localization in images. Specifically, it proposes a novel method for prior learning and active object localization using kernel-based density estimations. This falls under the sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of probabilistic representations and machine learning paradigms, which are relevant to sub-categories such as machine learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
